I suggest changing the order of tests to: _  _ if (operand == null || operand.isEmpty()) { _   logger.info("operand is empty")_ _ } else if (operand.contains(".")) { _   snssai = operand.substring(operand.lastIndexOf(".") + 1)_ _ } _  _ Note that if this is in a tight loop and becomes time-critical, this has the issue that operand is scanning the end of the string twice for ".". So another formulation would be: _  _ if (operand == null || operand.isEmpty()) { _   logger.info("operand is empty")_ _ } else { _   int dotLocation = operand.lastIndexOf(".")_ _   if (dotLocation != -1) { _     snssai = operand.substring(dotLocation + 1)_ _   } _ }
